<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6312&amp;p=60578#p60578"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">sahib wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />How can I tell whether a ROM assigned to mapper 1 is using any of the mapper subtypes, such as SUROM, SXROM and SOROM?<br /></div><br />If PRG ROM size is 524288 bytes and CHR ROM size is 0 bytes, the board is most likely SUROM. To know whether SOROM or SXROM is used, you have to recognize the SHA-1 value of a good dump or use <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/NES_2.0" class="postlink">NES 2.0</a> for hacks or homebrews.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Apr 29, 2010 4:59 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
