<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6312&amp;p=60569#p60569</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6312&amp;p=60569#p60569"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[MMC1 questions]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6312&amp;p=60569#p60569"><![CDATA[
99 % of games with CHR-RAM will swap the 8kb linearly at start up and will never touch this again (and Final Fantasy definitely does that). As far I know there is 2 exeptions : Romancia and Lagrange Point.<br /><br />CHR-RAM switching works just like CHR-ROM switching... in the case of the MMC1 you get either 1 8kb bank (that you can't switch) or 2 4kb banks. There is absolutely no use of this on the MMC1 because you can select which pattern table is used via $2000 anyway... but yet it's just because Nintendo decided to tie A12 on the cart to the MMC1 instead to directly the PPU A12 line.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Thu Apr 29, 2010 1:49 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
