hijacking this thread a bit, apologies all around <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />I'm implementing MMC1 as of now and I've got a few questions.<br /><br />How does CHR-RAM swapping work? I figured out CHR-ROM swapping and it works well, but so far my attempts on addressing CHR-RAM has been unfruitful. <br />A few games work fairly well without doing any actual swapping (metroid et al) but some refuse to boot (Final fantasy) and a few got graphical glitches (maniac mansion). Final fantasy not booting might be completely irrelevant and due to a bug someplace else. Anyway.<br />Is CHR-RAM just an 8kb memory area on board the cartridge (which I assume it is) which the PPU uses like it normally uses CHR-ROM? And if it is, what's the use of swapping? if anybody would be able to clear this up for me I'd much appreciate it!<br /><br />and finally, <br />How can I tell whether a ROM assigned to mapper 1 is using any of the mapper subtypes, such as SUROM, SXROM and SOROM?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4182">sahib</a> — Wed Apr 28, 2010 9:36 pm</p><hr />
