<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6312&amp;p=60403#p60403"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">oRBIT2002 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">1)<br />2) You can't tell. It is presumably random.<br /></div><br /><br />Is this 100% true? I've checked the game Bubble Bobble and it wants the CHR-banks in a special order or else it would obviously look wrong during the bootup-title sequence.<br />Perhaps my emulator is buggy but I don't trap any CHR-swaps during the intro of Bubble Bobble at all.</div><br />Some mappers (or some revisions of them) might have known powerup states but I don't think there's a central place that documents them. If you want to make sure your emulator is not the culprit you could trap in a known good emulator like Nintendulator.<br /><br />I checked Bubble Bobble in Nintendulator and it definitely is writing to CHR banking regs ($BFFF, $DFFF specifically) before intro sequence.<br /><br />For programming purposes it's the best practice to always assume everything is uninitialized/unknown on powerup.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">thefox</a> — Mon Apr 26, 2010 5:52 am</p><hr />
