<author><name><![CDATA[tokumaru]]></name></author>
<updated>2010-04-23T13:11:11-07:00</updated>
<published>2010-04-23T13:11:11-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6312&amp;p=60284#p60284</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6312&amp;p=60284#p60284"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[MMC1 questions]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6312&amp;p=60284#p60284"><![CDATA[
There is no rule that dictates what kind of mirroring a game has to use when scrolling in different directions. Every combination is possible, it only depends on how the scrolling engine is programmed. So just because a game scrolls both vertically and horizontally that doesn't mean it has to change the type of mirroring, otherwise games in carts with no mirroring control (most discrete logic mappers) would be limited to one type of scrolling, which is not the case.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Fri Apr 23, 2010 1:11 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
